article.description: Brandon Boyd hit two 3-pointers and scored 15 and Gary Chivichyan added 10 points to help Idaho State rally for a 74-66 victory over NAIA-member Montana-Western on Thursday night.
article.headline: Boyd leads Idaho St past Montana-Western 74-66
article.linkText: Boyd leads Idaho St past Montana-Western 74-66
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Brandon Boyd hit two 3-pointers and scored 15 and Gary Chivichyan added 10 points to help Idaho State rally for a 74-66 victory over NAIA-member Montana-Western on Thursday night. Chier Maker finished with nine points and nine rebounds for the Bengals (3-3), while Kelvin Jones scored nine with seven boards. Freshman Cedric Boone was a one-man show for the Bulldogs. He scored 19 of his 27 points in the first half to guide Montana-Western to a 33-31 lead at intermission. Boone made 6 of 10 from 3-point range and added four assists for the Bulldogs (3-2), who were playing an exhibition game. Back-to-back 3-pointers by Derrek Durocher -- his only points in the game -- gave Montana-Western a 48-41 advantage with 14:16 left to play. The Bengals answered with Maker's 3-pointer to cap an 11-0 run for a 52-48 lead. Boyd's 3-pointer with 4:03 remaining pushed the Bengals' lead to double digits and they held on from there. Idaho State outrebounded the Bulldogs 43-34 and had a 36-12 edge in points in the paint.
